msgctxt "sn48.51:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 6. Sūkarakhatavagga → sūkarakhātavaggo (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn48.51:0.2"
msgid "6. Sūkarakhatavagga "
msgstr "6. The Boar’s Cave "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 51. Sālasutta → sālāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn48.51:0.3"
msgid "51. Sālasutta "
msgstr "51. At Sālā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn48.51:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn48.51:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu viharati sālāya brāhmaṇagāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Kosalans near the brahmin village of Sālā. "

msgctxt "sn48.51:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

#. VAR: sūrena → sūriyena (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn48.51:1.4"
msgid "“seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci tiracchānagatā pāṇā, sīho migarājā tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ—thāmena javena sūrena; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, the lion, king of beasts, is said to be the best of animals in terms of strength, speed, and courage. "

msgctxt "sn48.51:1.5"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye keci bodhipakkhiyā dhammā, paññindriyaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ—bodhāya. "
msgstr "In the same way, the faculty of wisdom is said to be the best of the qualities that lead to awakening in terms of becoming awakened. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.228, sc2
msgctxt "sn48.51:2.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, bodhipakkhiyā dhammā? "
msgstr "And what are the qualities that lead to awakening? "

msgctxt "sn48.51:2.2"
msgid "Saddhindriyaṃ, bhikkhave, bodhipakkhiyo dhammo, taṃ bodhāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "The faculties of faith, "

msgctxt "sn48.51:2.3"
msgid "vīriyindriyaṃ bodhipakkhiyo dhammo, taṃ bodhāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "energy, "

msgctxt "sn48.51:2.4"
msgid "satindriyaṃ bodhipakkhiyo dhammo, taṃ bodhāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "mindfulness, "

msgctxt "sn48.51:2.5"
msgid "samādhindriyaṃ bodhipakkhiyo dhammo, taṃ bodhāya saṃvattati; "
msgstr "immersion, "

msgctxt "sn48.51:2.6"
msgid "paññindriyaṃ bodhipakkhiyo dhammo, taṃ bodhāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "and wisdom are qualities that lead to awakening, in that they lead to becoming awakened. "

msgctxt "sn48.51:2.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci tiracchānagatā pāṇā, sīho migarājā tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ—thāmena javena sūrena; "
msgstr "The lion, king of beasts, is said to be the best of animals in terms of strength, speed, and courage. "

msgctxt "sn48.51:2.8"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye keci bodhipakkhiyā dhammā, paññindriyaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ—bodhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, the faculty of wisdom is said to be the best of the qualities that lead to awakening in terms of becoming awakened.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.51:2.9"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

